result.name: R&R Bagels

reviews.text: Love this place. Great, fresh ingredients. Can get busy late morning and lunchtime, but the bagels are 👌🏻

I got the mocha coffee and strawberry & honey glazed bagel. The coffee was very good and the bagel was pretty good too. The place is kind of small - you gotta scoot yourself into the seats.

The staff also speaks English so you can order that way. The only thing is the items are pretty expensive for what they are (almost 100 HKD for the two items).

The look of the store pleases, it’s pretty stylish for a bagel shop: the floor, the furnishings, the overall mood, it just fits. But a shop should not only look good but also serve its purpose and sell goods, but that's exactly what it lacks. Far too few staff for the amount of customers, and the shop is not really big. Waiting almost 35 minutes for a bagel is simply too much, especially since it was filled with only 4 ingredients. At the same time, delivery orders went through the counter all the time, feeling that was their main business and that the customer in the shop was disturbing rather. The taste was good, but overpriced for the overall experience. Would I come back? No.

Great Bagels a really wide selection of options and their English is perfect so you can amend your orders from their sets. Gets busy at lunchtime.
No facilities for babies though
They stayed open late to sell us delicious bagels. Great people and great place
